# Open Home Club

Open Home Club
A non‑commercial platform for sharing homes, vehicles, and local support — outside licensing systems and short‑term rental platforms.
Open Home Club is an open, community‑driven classified board for people who want to use what they already have, without entering the commercial short‑term rental market.
This platform exists for two groups at the same time:

people who own underused spaces or vehicles,
people who travel or live flexibly and prefer human contact over platforms.

We are not a marketplace.
We do not process payments, take commissions, or act as intermediaries.

Why Open Home Club exists (the real problems it solves)
Many people today have assets that cannot be legally or practically rented on commercial platforms:


Apartments in Italy, Spain, or other countries that:

cannot obtain rental licenses,
don’t meet technical requirements (layout, ceiling height, cadastral category),
are blocked by local regulations limiting short‑term rentals,
stand empty most of the year while still generating costs.



Camper vans, vans, boats, or vehicles that:

are used only a few weeks per year,
are expensive to maintain,
are often sold only because “they’re not being used enough”.



People who could share instead of rent, but:

don’t want to operate in the grey market,
don’t qualify for official rental platforms,
don’t want to become mini‑hoteliers.



Open Home Club creates space for cost‑sharing, reciprocity, and community use — without becoming a rental platform.

What you can find here
Listings may include:


Shared spaces

homes, apartments, rooms, sofas,
land, gardens, camping spots,
parking for cars or camper vans.



Shared mobility

camper vans, vans, cars, boats,
offered non‑commercially.



Local support (“Helping Hand”)

orientation in a foreign place,
help for people who don’t speak the local language,
everyday assistance or human backup in unfamiliar situations.



Each listing clearly states:

intent: offering or looking for,
form of reciprocity:

no expectations,
cost contribution,
help on site,
barter / exchange,
individually agreed.




Who this platform is especially for

Owners whose properties cannot be rented commercially due to regulations.
Camper and van owners who want to share instead of sell.
People who prefer co‑use over ownership pressure.
Travelers who:

don’t speak many languages,
prefer staying connected to real people,
want alternatives to Airbnb and Booking.



Open Home Club opens travel and sharing to people who are excluded by current platforms.

What Open Home Club is NOT

Not Airbnb, Booking, or a rental marketplace.
Not a parking platform or vehicle rental service.
Not a job or paid service platform.
Not an intermediary, guarantor, or licensing bypass.

The platform only enables direct contact.
All agreements are voluntary and made between people.

Language & accessibility
The interface is in Polish.
All listing descriptions can be automatically translated into other European languages with one click.
Machine translations are clearly marked.

Why this matters
Because current platforms:

leave many people with unused assets,
block non‑standard housing and mobility,
reward optimization, not reciprocity.

Open Home Club is an open experiment in trust‑based sharing, outside algorithmic marketplaces.
If this resonates with you — you’re in the right place.
